#####################################################
### How to use Burgogne in ALYA
#####################################################

1.Compile openssl
   cd Thirdparties/openssl-1.1.0e
   ./config
   make
   make test

2. Compile Burgogne
   cd ../Burgogne/
   make lib
   make test

3. Compile Alya
   Add / uncomment the following lines in the Alya configure FILE:

   CSALYA     := $(CSALYA) -DBOURGOGNE
   EXTRALIB   := $(EXTRALIB) -L../../Thirdparties/Burgogne -lburgogne
   EXTRALIB   := $(EXTRALIB) -L../../Thirdparties/openssl-1.1.0e -lcrypto -lssl -Wl,-rpath=$(PWD)/../../Thirdparties/openssl-1.1.0e

   Compile Alya as usual.

